Package: hydflood
Type: Package
Title: Algorithms to compute flood extent and duration along the German federal 
    waterways Elbe and Rhine
Version: 0.4.0
Date: 2022-07-19
Authors@R: c(person("Arnd", "Weber", email = "arnd.weber@bafg.de",
                    role = c("aut", "cre"), 
                    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5973-2770")),
            person("Stephan", "Rosenzweig", email = "rosenzweig@bafg.de",
                    role = c("ctb")))
Description: hydflood extends the functionalities of hyd1d, an R package to 
    interpolate 1D water level and gauging data, to raster based GIS processing. 
    hydflood adopts strategies originally developed for INFORM, an 
    ArcGIS-based hydro-ecological modelling framework, to compute flood extent 
    and duration. It does not provide a full, physical hydraulic modelling 
    algorithm, but a simplified, near realtime GIS approach for flood 
    extent and duration modelling.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), sf, terra, raster, hyd1d, hoardr
